<span> How to Incorporate the Google Translate Plug-in Into Your Website </span>

<p>The internet is continuing to grow and has become the default communication for businesses and individuals looking for goods, services, or information. For companies looking to gain a competitive advantage, that means expanding your client base and increasing sales volumes.</p> 

<p>The internet originally began as an English speaking convention, and in the beginning it was dominated by English speakers and users. Having a multilingual site is one of the best ways to market your company, bringing in a new audience of users and creating new relationships.</p> 

<p>Let’s say you have a website already completed, but want to add in different language selections to your site.</p> 

<span>How to add the google translate widget to your site:</span> <br>

<span>1. Visit the Google Translation Manager, sign into your Google Account (if you don’t have an account already, you can sign up for a free Google account).</span> <br>

<span>2. Click the ‘Add to your website now’ on the right­hand side.</span> <br>

<span>3. Follow the instructions on the next few pages to customize your translator, which includes the various languages you can choose to add to your site.</span> <br> 

<span>4. Add the widget code to the page where you’d like your translator to show up, add the widget/html element and paste in the widget code.</span> <br>

<span>Make sure when coding to give enough space design wise for various word interpretations.</span> 
	
